
[1]fanciful

   FAN'CIFUL, a. [See Fancy.]

   1. Guided by the imagination, rather than by reason and experience;
   subject to the influence of fancy; whimsical; applied to persons. A
   fanciful man forms visionary projects.

   2. Dictated by the imagination; full of wild images; chimerical;
   whimsical; ideal; visionary; applied to things; as a fanciful scheme; a
   fanciful theory.
